@startuml SCRUM-7 Logout Sequence Diagram

title Secure Logout – SCRUM-7

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor       User        as U
participant "Browser"   as B
participant "SecurityFilter\n@WebFilter(/*)" as SF
participant "LogoutServlet\nPOST /logout" as LS
participant "HttpSession"  as S
participant "AuthFilter\n@WebFilter(/protected/*)" as AF

== Logout Flow ==

U  -> B  : Click "Logout" button
B  -> SF : POST /logout\n(with JSESSIONID cookie)
activate SF
SF -> SF : Set security headers\n(X-Frame-Options, CSP, …)
SF -> LS : filterChain.doFilter()
deactivate SF

activate LS
LS -> S  : getSession(false)
activate S
S  --> LS : HttpSession (non-null)
deactivate S

LS -> S  : invalidate()
activate S
note right of S : Session removed from server;\nJSESSIONID cookie invalidated
S  --> LS : (void)
deactivate S

LS -> LS : Set no-cache headers\n(Cache-Control, Pragma, Expires)
LS -> B  : 302 Redirect → /login
deactivate LS

B  -> U  : Render login page

== Attempt to Access Protected Page After Logout ==

U  -> B  : Navigate to /protected/dashboard
B  -> SF : GET /protected/dashboard\n(no valid JSESSIONID)
activate SF
SF -> AF : filterChain.doFilter()
deactivate SF

activate AF
AF -> S  : getSession(false)
activate S
S  --> AF : null  (session was invalidated)
deactivate S

AF -> B  : 302 Redirect → /login
deactivate AF
note over B : User cannot access protected\npage after logout

@enduml
